he felt confident,

23
00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:31.420
assured that he was going to get in,
but failure struck him like lightening.

24
00:01:31.840 --> 00:01:35.620
His drawings were judged as unsatisfactory and he was told he had a lack of

25
00:01:35.621 --> 00:01:39.160
artistic talent with a notable lack of appreciation for the human form.

26
00:01:41.140 --> 00:01:44.050
Shaken,
heartbroken and rejected.

27
00:01:44.410 --> 00:01:48.430
He left Vienna and returned home planning to take the entrance exam next year,

28
00:01:49.630 --> 00:01:51.190
but things didn't quite go to plan for him.

29
00:01:51.490 --> 00:01:56.260
The next year he failed the exam again and his beloved mother died after a long

30
00:01:56.261 --> 00:01:57.160
battle with cancer.

31
00:01:58.090 --> 00:02:00.670
It wasn't long before he ran out of money and was forced to live in homeless

32
